WEBVTT

00:00.152 --> 00:01.705
Previously on
<i>The Client List...</i>

00:01.708 --> 00:03.869
What kind of man takes advantage
of his brother's wife?

00:05.774 --> 00:06.630
Evan, what happened?

00:06.655 --> 00:08.182
Construction and I
are on the outs.

00:08.237 --> 00:10.304
It might be time for me
to find a new line of work.

00:10.339 --> 00:12.078
Evan's gonna be a cop,
and you're a --

00:12.103 --> 00:13.541
Business owner?

00:13.542 --> 00:15.476
Now we got clients
coming out of our asses.

00:15.511 --> 00:16.878
I'm getting ready to hire
some new girls myself.

00:16.912 --> 00:18.946
How do I know who to trust?
Follow your gut.

00:18.981 --> 00:21.649
Who the hell are you?
This is our new girl, Nikki.

00:21.684 --> 00:22.884
Welcome
to the family.

00:22.918 --> 00:24.519
If Kyle's pulled you
into something,

00:24.553 --> 00:26.054
it won't just be the money
or your freedom you could lose.

00:26.088 --> 00:27.689
It'll be your family.
I just can't take anymore --

00:27.723 --> 00:30.491
between the kids
and mama's accident.

00:30.526 --> 00:31.893
Your mom told me
the bail hearing happened.

00:31.927 --> 00:34.362
How'd it go?
Do you happen to have $7,500?

00:34.396 --> 00:38.066
This is for Kyle's bail.
I did all of this for you.

00:38.100 --> 00:40.134
Do you like
what you do here?

00:40.169 --> 00:42.537
I love what I do. I get to
put my P.T. training to use.

00:42.571 --> 00:44.238
You give a good interview.

00:44.273 --> 00:46.507
Welcome to
the Rub of Sugar Land.

00:46.542 --> 00:47.928
Riley, is there something going
on with you and my brother?

00:47.953 --> 00:48.776
I don't know.

00:48.777 --> 00:50.545
If you don't want to
take his money, that's fine,

00:50.579 --> 00:52.099
but we're out of options.
Pay the bail.

00:53.882 --> 00:57.051
Riley: Oh, Dashiell,
London sounds amazing.

00:57.086 --> 00:58.419
I would die to go.

00:58.454 --> 01:01.556
Oh, it's a great city,
Riley,

01:01.590 --> 01:04.158
but it's a lot of traveling
for one game.

01:04.193 --> 01:07.261
Preseason was a blast
when I was younger, and now...

01:07.296 --> 01:11.165
Well, I could never
get tired of that --

01:11.200 --> 01:13.568
your life.
It seems great.

01:13.602 --> 01:16.104
Pro ball gives you
everything that you want.

01:16.138 --> 01:18.673
Travel,
packed stadiums, money.

01:18.707 --> 01:21.175
[ Grunts ]
Women.

01:21.210 --> 01:22.543
Exactly.

01:22.578 --> 01:25.546
There's just times
when you want more.

01:25.581 --> 01:29.083
Not more...
just different.

01:29.118 --> 01:32.253
After a while,
the thrill is gone.

01:32.287 --> 01:34.255
Except here.

01:34.289 --> 01:36.457
Well,
I'll show you thrilling.

01:36.492 --> 01:38.359
Ooh. All righty.

01:38.393 --> 01:40.361
[ Sighs ]

01:40.395 --> 01:42.363
♪ I want it all

01:42.397 --> 01:44.198
God, you're beautiful.

01:44.233 --> 01:46.567
I bet there is not
a dull moment in your life.

01:46.602 --> 01:47.802
Oh.
[ Grunts ]

01:47.836 --> 01:50.238
You have no idea.

01:50.272 --> 01:52.640
Both:
Mud pie! Mud pie!

01:52.674 --> 01:54.642
Yeah, I know
that they look like mud pies,

01:54.676 --> 01:55.943
but they're actually scones.

01:55.978 --> 01:58.312
What happened
to our pancakes?

01:58.347 --> 01:59.881
Well, mama wanted to try
something different.

01:59.915 --> 02:01.916
Is that because
daddy's coming home today?

02:01.950 --> 02:04.051
Maybe.
Both: Daddy's coming home!

02:04.086 --> 02:06.587
Daddy's coming home!
Daddy's coming home!

02:06.622 --> 02:08.055
Yay!
[ Laughs ]

02:08.090 --> 02:09.723
The kids
make this mess?

02:09.758 --> 02:12.126
No, that was me,
and you're not helping.

02:12.161 --> 02:14.595
Hey, is your shoulder
still hurting you?

02:14.630 --> 02:15.930
You're supposed to re
in your sling.

02:15.964 --> 02:17.398
It's nothing
I can't handle,

02:17.432 --> 02:19.500
which is more than I can say
about your scones.

02:19.535 --> 02:20.935
Are they too hard?
[ Chuckles ]

02:20.969 --> 02:22.904
They have a certain density.
[ Laughs ]

02:22.938 --> 02:24.618
You know what?
I threw out the first batch,

02:24.640 --> 02:26.240
and I'm sorry
that I'm more of a pancake girl

02:26.275 --> 02:27.775
and I didn't get
your baking gene.

02:27.810 --> 02:29.811
Well, "A" for effort,
and if the kids won't eat these,

02:29.845 --> 02:31.779
you can always use it
as a hockey puck.

02:31.814 --> 02:33.581
[ Laughing ] Mama!
[ Doorbell rings ]

02:33.615 --> 02:34.882
I'll get
the kids ready.

02:36.285 --> 02:38.953
Hey! Come on in.
Morning.

02:38.987 --> 02:41.355
Wow,
you look --

02:41.390 --> 02:42.924
Busy.
I know.

02:42.958 --> 02:44.659
Not really what I was gonna say,
but okay.

02:44.693 --> 02:46.427
Hey, thanks for
taking the kids to school.

02:46.461 --> 02:47.862
Today just got crazy
around here.

02:47.896 --> 02:49.330
Of course.

02:49.364 --> 02:51.098
You okay?
Yeah, yeah. I'm fine.

02:51.133 --> 02:53.434
It's just, you know,
Kyle's hearing is today

02:53.468 --> 02:55.369
and he's gonna get out,
and once that happens,

02:55.404 --> 02:57.471
I'm just not quite sure
how I'm gonna handle that.

02:57.506 --> 02:59.440
Same way you've been handling
this past year.

02:59.474 --> 03:01.008
Yeah, well,
it's not that simple.

03:01.043 --> 03:03.311
I went to see him a few days
ago, and he knows about us.

03:03.345 --> 03:05.379
I know.

03:05.414 --> 03:07.014
You know?

03:07.049 --> 03:09.483
What do you think
our fight was about

03:09.518 --> 03:11.986
when you bailed me
out of jail?

03:12.020 --> 03:13.120
I probably should have
said something before.

03:13.155 --> 03:14.722
Yeah, well,
you didn't.

03:17.326 --> 03:19.894
Riley, I was just trying
to make things easier

03:19.928 --> 03:22.063
for you, for us.

03:24.900 --> 03:26.734
You have
a little flour.

03:26.768 --> 03:28.402
[ Both laugh ]
Sorry.

03:28.437 --> 03:30.671
You mean
the world to me.

03:32.574 --> 03:35.376
I just want to be able to say it
out loud to you, to everyone.

03:35.410 --> 03:37.678
You know what? The kids
are right down the hall.

03:37.713 --> 03:39.046
Oh, hey.

03:39.081 --> 03:40.615
Uncle Evan!
Okay, let's go to school.

03:40.649 --> 03:41.949
Uncle Evan, let's go.

03:41.984 --> 03:44.619
Okay, hey, kisses, please.
Thank you.

03:44.653 --> 03:46.354
[ Smooches ]
Okay.

03:46.388 --> 03:47.655
I love you. Go.

03:47.689 --> 03:50.057
I'll call you later.
Uh-huh.

03:50.092 --> 03:51.626
Aah!
Oh, sorry.

03:51.660 --> 03:53.895
Time to switch those two
to decaf. Geez.

03:53.929 --> 03:55.296
What's the story,
morning glory?

03:55.330 --> 03:56.731
Let's move out.

03:56.765 --> 03:58.833
Hair extensions and dye jobs
wait for no woman.

03:58.867 --> 04:00.668
Be right with you. Oh!
Oh, mama, are you okay?

04:00.702 --> 04:04.038
Oh, I'm fine.
I'm sorry about the pitcher.

04:04.072 --> 04:06.040
Oh, don't worry.
We'll clean it up.

04:06.074 --> 04:08.075
Are you sure that you're ready
to go back to work?

04:08.110 --> 04:09.543
It's nothing.
I have clients.

04:09.578 --> 04:11.846
Okay, well, did you think about
what I asked?

04:11.880 --> 04:13.214
I'm not
moving in with you.

04:13.248 --> 04:15.683
You've got enough
on your plate right now.

04:15.717 --> 04:17.752
Besides, I can
take care of myself.

04:17.786 --> 04:22.055
Now, I'm going to work, which is
exactly what you should do.

04:22.089 --> 04:24.258
Is that understood?
Yes, ma'am.

04:24.293 --> 04:26.594
Here. Breakfast.
Oh, thank you.

04:26.628 --> 04:27.895
[ Clears throat ]

04:27.930 --> 04:29.864
I wouldn't
if I were you.

04:29.898 --> 04:31.232
[ Scone thuds ]

04:31.257 --> 04:35.257
<font color=#00FF00>♪ The Client List 2x04 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>My Main Trial Is Yet to Come</font>
Original Air Date on March 31, 2013

04:35.258 --> 04:39.758
== sync, corrected by <font color="#00FF00">elderman</font> ==

04:40.091 --> 04:41.925
Thank you
for bringing my suit.

04:41.959 --> 04:43.159
Yeah,
of course.

04:43.194 --> 04:45.328
After our
last conversation,

04:45.363 --> 04:46.997
I wasn't sure
when I'd see you again.

04:47.031 --> 04:49.332
Kyle, I got you a lawyer
and I paid your bail

04:49.367 --> 04:51.468
because I wanted
to get you out of here.

04:51.502 --> 04:54.070
But we really can't
keep having this conversation.

04:54.105 --> 04:56.406
I know,
and I'm sorry...

04:56.440 --> 04:59.075
for everything.

04:59.110 --> 05:02.278
I want you to know how much I
appreciate all that you've done.

05:06.050 --> 05:07.283
Uh, here.

05:07.318 --> 05:08.818
Kids made that
for you.

05:08.853 --> 05:10.787
That thing in there
is a donkey.

05:10.821 --> 05:14.691
Travis is big on donkeys
these days.

05:14.725 --> 05:16.192
[ Chuckles ]

05:16.227 --> 05:18.128
Tell him
I love him.

05:18.162 --> 05:19.596
I will.

05:19.630 --> 05:23.133
Man, are they excited
to see you.

05:23.167 --> 05:25.969
I can't wait
to see them.

05:26.003 --> 05:28.438
I miss them
so much.

05:28.472 --> 05:30.473
Yeah, we'll have to figure out
a time or a place

05:30.508 --> 05:31.875
once you
get out of here.

05:31.909 --> 05:34.944
Well, you'll bring them
to the hearing?

05:34.979 --> 05:36.179
Please.

05:36.213 --> 05:39.349
Oh, I don't know
about that.

05:39.383 --> 05:41.618
Riley, it'd mean the world
to me if they were there.

05:41.652 --> 05:43.653
I don't -- I don't think
a jail or a courtroom

05:43.687 --> 05:45.321
is the right place.

05:45.356 --> 05:47.023
You're just gonna have to see
them the second you get home.

05:47.058 --> 05:49.626
Well, will you come?

05:49.660 --> 05:52.529
I know
that it's a lot to ask.

05:52.563 --> 05:54.064
I know you got work.

05:54.098 --> 05:57.000
It'd be a huge help
if you were there.

05:57.034 --> 06:01.071
Yeah,
of course I'll be there.

06:04.675 --> 06:08.878
Okay, well...

06:08.913 --> 06:11.681
I'll be there.

06:11.715 --> 06:12.749
Thank you.

06:30.367 --> 06:32.001
Okay,
morning, everyone.

06:32.036 --> 06:34.571
I just want to say that
all of you guys are amazing.

06:34.605 --> 06:36.806
Over the past month,
profits are up 62%.

06:36.841 --> 06:38.575
Our client feedback
has been stellar,

06:38.609 --> 06:40.310
and it's all
because of you ladies.

06:40.344 --> 06:42.712
And gentleman.
Well, thank you, darlin'.

06:42.746 --> 06:44.013
You know what?
Pamela brings up a great point.

06:44.048 --> 06:46.149
Derek, you get
an extra shout-out today

06:46.183 --> 06:48.685
because you have built up
our female client base

06:48.719 --> 06:50.553
faster than I could have
ever expected,

06:50.588 --> 06:52.555
and your repeat clients --
very impressive.

06:52.590 --> 06:54.724
So, great work.
Can somebody please let her in?

06:54.758 --> 06:56.226
Sorry.
All right, y'all.

06:56.260 --> 06:57.994
Let's go and make
some people happy, huh?

06:58.028 --> 06:59.496
Okay, Selena,
Nikki, Pamela,

06:59.530 --> 07:01.297
I need to speak
to y'all privately.

07:03.467 --> 07:05.568
Sorry I'm late.
I hope you got my message.

07:05.603 --> 07:07.036
What message?
This morning.

07:07.071 --> 07:09.205
I left a message
at the front desk with Selena.

07:09.240 --> 07:11.741
Oh, yeah. Pippi Longstockings
might be late. Mm-hmm.

07:11.775 --> 07:13.343
Okay,
I just wanted to remind y'all

07:13.377 --> 07:15.111
to tell your client list clients

07:15.146 --> 07:17.080
that they can use the private
V.I.P. entrance in the back.

07:17.114 --> 07:18.915
It's gonna be a lot more secure,
and remember,

07:18.949 --> 07:21.718
no "special treatment" talk
in the lobby.

07:21.752 --> 07:24.587
You got it. And before you go,
I've got some great news.

07:24.622 --> 07:25.855
Look!

07:25.890 --> 07:27.457
Okay, what am I looking at?

07:27.491 --> 07:31.060
A semester full
of college extension courses.

07:31.095 --> 07:33.463
Oh, I was off
having two kids.

07:33.497 --> 07:36.065
Yeah, I mean, I never saw myself
getting my degree, either,

07:36.100 --> 07:38.801
but now that I've got the money,
stability, and support...

07:38.836 --> 07:40.904
Well, your clients love you,
and so do we.

07:40.938 --> 07:42.138
Now get to work.
Well...

07:42.173 --> 07:43.439
[ Laughs ]

07:43.474 --> 07:46.743
...keep the clients coming.
Dirty.

07:47.745 --> 07:49.245
Okay.

07:54.952 --> 07:56.152
We've got a problem.

07:56.187 --> 07:57.754
Oh,
and Debbie Downer's back.

07:57.788 --> 07:59.589
Someone's been snooping around.
My lock's been jimmied.

07:59.623 --> 08:00.990
Well, maybe you
forgot to lock it.

08:01.025 --> 08:02.625
Oh, yeah,
and maybe I'm still a virgin.

08:02.660 --> 08:03.927
Anything's possible.

08:03.961 --> 08:05.895
[ Laughs ] Virgin.
I have a client.

08:05.930 --> 08:07.797
No, my stuff
has been messed with.

08:07.831 --> 08:09.432
I ain't
gonna let it slide.

08:09.466 --> 08:11.334
I think
it's that new girl, Nikki.

08:11.368 --> 08:12.936
Really? Nikki?
Oh, come on.

08:12.970 --> 08:15.405
She is too perky, always getting
in everyone's business.

08:15.439 --> 08:17.140
Who smiles that much?
She's friendly!

08:17.174 --> 08:18.975
Oh, I don't trust her.
You don't trust anyone.

08:18.976 --> 08:20.677
Maybe it's
a you problem.

08:23.214 --> 08:26.316
God,
you look like an angel.

08:26.350 --> 08:28.284
Yeah, well,
you said you wanted different.

08:28.319 --> 08:29.986
I can be
whatever you want me to be.

08:30.020 --> 08:31.788
Are you sure
this is not too much oil?

08:31.822 --> 08:33.923
No, no.
It feels great.

08:33.957 --> 08:35.592
Okay, a little more?

08:35.626 --> 08:37.327
The more, the merrier.

08:37.361 --> 08:41.431
All right, well, gives new"

08:41.465 --> 08:43.832
Oh, maybe --
maybe just a little more.

08:43.866 --> 08:46.269
Okay.

08:46.303 --> 08:47.804
What is going on?

08:47.838 --> 08:50.473
Is everything okay?
[ Sighs ]

08:50.507 --> 08:52.375
I'm sorry.
It's not you.

08:52.409 --> 08:53.743
I'm just stressed.

08:53.777 --> 08:55.278
Big game tomorrow,

08:55.312 --> 08:57.347
and this new offensive
coordinator is driving me nuts.

08:57.381 --> 08:59.115
He must be
getting on your nerves

08:59.149 --> 09:00.650
'cause usually
when you're stressed out,

09:00.684 --> 09:02.785
this extra oil
does the trick.

09:02.820 --> 09:04.621
I know,
and you're great.

09:04.655 --> 09:07.190
But, you know,
we've done the extra oil before.

09:07.224 --> 09:09.058
Okay, so,
what do you want to do?

09:09.093 --> 09:10.827
Might take
some preparation.

09:10.861 --> 09:12.395
No,
that's okay.

09:12.429 --> 09:14.731
I can always make
a special appointment for you.

09:14.765 --> 09:16.566
Have you ever
heard of sploshing?

09:27.878 --> 09:29.479
Evan: Hey.
[ Cellphone beeps ]

09:29.513 --> 09:31.080
Oh, hey.
Uh, hey.

09:31.115 --> 09:32.982
What are you doing here?
Kyle's hearing.

09:33.017 --> 09:35.685
I thought, uh, you might need
some moral support.

09:35.719 --> 09:37.086
Oh,
you didn't have to come.

09:37.121 --> 09:38.354
I know.

09:38.389 --> 09:40.023
I wanted to.
For you.

09:42.259 --> 09:44.494
That's really --
that's really nice of you.

09:44.528 --> 09:46.596
But you don't want me
to be here.

09:46.630 --> 09:48.865
No, it's not that.
It's just, you know,

09:48.899 --> 09:51.501
I mean, Kyle's got to
get through this hearing,

09:51.535 --> 09:54.537
and, well, there's some stuff
to work out for you and I.

09:54.571 --> 09:55.772
Yeah, I get it.

09:55.806 --> 09:57.040
Just, um...

09:57.074 --> 09:59.509
You know,
I just wanted to help.

09:59.543 --> 10:01.110
I know that.

10:02.646 --> 10:04.247
I'm sorry. I just have to
get through today.

10:04.281 --> 10:05.515
Can you
understand that?

10:05.549 --> 10:07.116
Yeah, of course.
Okay. Thank you.

10:07.151 --> 10:08.418
I'll call you tonight.

10:08.452 --> 10:09.719
I promise.
Okay.

10:16.393 --> 10:18.528
Judge: Mr. Parks,
the court has confirmed

10:18.562 --> 10:21.097
that your bondsman
has posted your bail of $75,000.

10:21.131 --> 10:22.932
Barring any objections,

10:22.966 --> 10:24.767
you will be released
on your own recognizance.

10:24.768 --> 10:27.370
Your Honor,
the prosecution moves

10:27.404 --> 10:29.105
to revoke all bail
from Mr. Parks.

10:29.139 --> 10:31.140
On what grounds?
Newly acquired evidence.

10:31.175 --> 10:34.210
Within the past year, Mr. Parks
has been identified in Mexico,

10:34.244 --> 10:36.879
associating with known members
of the Nogales drug cartel.

10:36.914 --> 10:38.715
Kyle:
That's insane!

10:38.749 --> 10:39.916
As a result,
the Mexican government

10:39.950 --> 10:41.250
has placed him
on a watch list.

10:41.285 --> 10:42.985
We believe
Mr. Parks to be a flight risk

10:43.020 --> 10:45.421
and a danger to society.
Graham: What?

10:45.456 --> 10:46.789
This is a stunt,
Your Honor!

10:46.824 --> 10:48.591
Counsel, approach.

10:48.625 --> 10:51.094
Defense strenuously objects.
What is happening?

10:51.128 --> 10:52.762
How come this is the first time
we're seeing this?

10:52.796 --> 10:54.263
It just came across my desk,
Your Honor.

10:54.298 --> 10:55.798
We haven't even had a chance
to review it.

10:55.833 --> 10:58.735
Noted for the record.
You may step back.

11:00.804 --> 11:04.707
Mr. Parks,
in light of this new evidence,

11:04.742 --> 11:06.709
bail is hereby revoked,

11:06.744 --> 11:09.245
and you are remanded
into custody until trial.

11:09.279 --> 11:10.813
None of that is true!
Bailiff.

11:10.848 --> 11:12.715
Wait, wait. Your Honor,
we haven't had an opportunity --

11:12.750 --> 11:14.083
None of that is true.
Kyle --

11:14.118 --> 11:15.952
None of that --
you got to believe me.

11:15.986 --> 11:17.720
Order!

11:17.755 --> 11:19.322
[ Indistinct conversations ]

11:28.131 --> 11:29.829
Kids, when
your mama gets home,

11:29.831 --> 11:31.899
I want you
to give her a great, big hug.

11:31.933 --> 11:33.601
Daddy, too.

11:35.403 --> 11:37.905
Should we tell them?
Riley's on her way back.

11:37.939 --> 11:39.473
We should
probably wait.

11:39.507 --> 11:41.575
Kids have plenty of time
to be sad.

11:41.610 --> 11:44.545
[ Door opens ]
Both: Daddy!

11:44.579 --> 11:45.813
[ Door closes ]

11:47.648 --> 11:49.649
Where's daddy?

11:51.619 --> 11:55.155
Uh, your daddy
couldn't come home yet.

11:55.189 --> 11:59.826
The judge needed to ask him
a few more questions, so...

11:59.861 --> 12:02.462
It's gonna be
just a little bit longer.

12:02.497 --> 12:04.464
I knew it!

12:04.499 --> 12:06.266
I'm never
gonna see daddy again!

12:06.300 --> 12:08.535
Never!

12:15.710 --> 12:19.112
Yeah. Uh...

12:19.147 --> 12:21.281
I'm gonna go
and take care of them.

12:22.650 --> 12:23.850
Y'all can wait.

12:23.885 --> 12:25.152
We're not
going anywhere.

12:26.821 --> 12:28.822
Okay.

12:33.394 --> 12:36.830
Nine lullabies
and three bedtime stories

12:36.864 --> 12:39.266
and they finally
cried themselves to sleep.

12:39.300 --> 12:40.667
I'm so sorry.

12:40.701 --> 12:42.335
We weren't sure
if we should tell them.

12:42.370 --> 12:43.870
You did
the right thing.

12:43.905 --> 12:46.606
You okay?

12:46.641 --> 12:50.510
Numb.
It all happened so fast.

12:50.545 --> 12:54.514
They called Kyle
a drug dealer.

12:54.549 --> 12:56.016
This is awful.

12:56.050 --> 12:58.485
No telling what that boy did
in Mexico.

12:58.519 --> 12:59.853
Mama, please.

13:03.090 --> 13:05.292
So, what about
Travis and Katie?

13:05.326 --> 13:08.495
I mean, now that Kyle's gonna be
in jail until the trial,

13:08.529 --> 13:10.630
are you gonna take them
to see him?

13:10.665 --> 13:11.865
I don't know.

13:11.899 --> 13:13.867
Of course not.

13:13.901 --> 13:15.702
You've got to
protect those kids.

13:15.736 --> 13:17.270
Back me up, Lacey.

13:17.305 --> 13:20.006
If Travis and Katie
see their dad in a jail cell,

13:20.041 --> 13:21.875
they'll never
be the same again.

13:25.646 --> 13:28.715
[ Sighs ]

13:37.191 --> 13:39.693
[ Doorknob rattling ]

13:41.596 --> 13:44.197
What in the lord?

13:46.200 --> 13:48.635
What are you doing?
Checking the locks.

13:48.669 --> 13:51.471
Now, I think someone
tried to pick yours, too.

13:51.505 --> 13:54.574
My locks are fine, and you
look like a crazy person.

13:54.609 --> 13:56.176
By the way,
if I was gonna blame someone,

13:56.210 --> 13:57.744
it would be you.
Oh, please.

13:57.778 --> 13:59.746
Anyone gonna break in here,
it's gonna be Nikki.

13:59.780 --> 14:01.848
Unh-unh. Anything else
you need to talk about?

14:01.883 --> 14:04.317
Um...
[ Sighs ]

14:04.352 --> 14:06.753
Here.
They're recipes.

14:06.787 --> 14:08.755
I heard
you had a splosher,

14:08.789 --> 14:10.257
and homemade pies
are a nice touch.

14:10.291 --> 14:11.524
Wow!

14:11.559 --> 14:14.861
Selena, wow.
I am really...

14:14.896 --> 14:17.163
What?
...Surprised.

14:17.198 --> 14:20.200
That I knew what a splosher was?
That you can bake.

14:20.234 --> 14:21.635
Why you people think
I can't do anything?

14:21.669 --> 14:23.036
They're color-coded.
I mean --

14:23.070 --> 14:24.871
know what? Forget it.
Give 'em back. Forget it.

14:24.906 --> 14:26.573
I'm sorry.
Really.

14:26.607 --> 14:29.743
I'm -- I'm gonna -- I'm gonna
bake me some pies, so...

14:29.777 --> 14:32.979
You know.

14:33.014 --> 14:35.715
You're welcome.
Yeah, yeah, okay. Sure.

14:35.750 --> 14:38.084
I still think
that someone's snooping around.

14:38.119 --> 14:39.352
Will you let it go?

14:39.387 --> 14:41.221
You can't trust new people.
Oh, why not?

14:41.255 --> 14:42.756
Because they are new,
all right?

14:42.790 --> 14:45.191
You can hire 'em, but you got to
watch 'em like a hawk.

14:45.226 --> 14:46.493
Ladies.

14:48.429 --> 14:52.132
Oh, is it just me or does he
get sexier every morning?

14:52.166 --> 14:53.366
[ Sighs ]

14:53.401 --> 14:55.502
Like a hawk.

14:55.536 --> 14:57.404
All right?

15:01.075 --> 15:03.510
Your shoulders
are really tight, Lisa.

15:03.544 --> 15:04.844
I know.

15:04.879 --> 15:07.216
I think I pulled something
in tennis.

15:07.585 --> 15:09.234
I've been playing
so much of it lately,

15:09.235 --> 15:10.936
what with my husband
on yet another business trip.

15:11.033 --> 15:11.035
Does he travel a lot?

15:11.036 --> 15:12.383
Gone six months
out of the year.

15:13.630 --> 15:15.531
But that's okay.
[ Chuckles ]

15:15.537 --> 15:19.440
Most of my friends
would kill for that free time.

15:19.474 --> 15:23.544
Your hands
are so perfect.

15:23.578 --> 15:26.347
You know, it's not --
it's not so much my shoulder

15:26.381 --> 15:28.449
but more my upper chest.

15:28.483 --> 15:32.720
You know,
where I swing my racket.

15:32.754 --> 15:36.123
Yeah, sure.

15:36.158 --> 15:39.059
[ Sighs ]

15:39.094 --> 15:41.061
More like here?

15:41.096 --> 15:44.165
Yeah.
That's the spot.

15:44.199 --> 15:46.967
You feel
that knot?

15:47.002 --> 15:51.372
Not so much a knot,
but it's tight.

15:51.406 --> 15:52.640
You're close.

15:52.674 --> 15:55.209
You mind
if I show you where?

15:55.243 --> 15:57.411
No.
No, not at all.

16:02.617 --> 16:05.085
More like there.

16:05.120 --> 16:07.922
Ma'am, I don't know.

16:07.956 --> 16:10.357
First of all,
never call me "ma'am."

16:11.593 --> 16:16.330
Second, you'll make
an incredibly lonely woman

16:16.364 --> 16:18.532
very happy.

16:18.567 --> 16:20.768
No one has to know.

16:23.738 --> 16:25.005
[ Chuckles ]

16:25.040 --> 16:28.008
I'll make it
worth your while.

16:28.043 --> 16:29.877
[ Sighs ]

16:34.649 --> 16:36.250
You wouldn't believe
what Mary Jo did.

16:36.284 --> 16:37.551
She's just awful.
[ Laughs ]

16:37.586 --> 16:40.020
I know.
[ Laughs ]

16:40.055 --> 16:41.555
Where you been?

16:41.590 --> 16:43.691
Well, if you must know,
I was in the bathroom.

16:43.725 --> 16:45.392
Why is that
a secret?

16:45.427 --> 16:47.194
It's not a secret.
I was just taking a test.

16:47.229 --> 16:49.396
Dale and I are trying to get
pregnant, and I thought...

16:49.431 --> 16:51.532
No. Negative.

16:51.566 --> 16:53.534
But we sure are
having fun trying.

16:53.568 --> 16:55.803
[ Laughs ] Anyway,
as I was saying, Inez,

16:55.837 --> 16:57.304
Billy Ray didn't even
get her a real diamond.

16:57.339 --> 16:58.606
[ Laughing ] No.
[ Groans ]

16:58.640 --> 17:00.941
Oh, oh, Linette!
Oh, you're burning me!

17:00.976 --> 17:02.743
Inez,
you are gonna be just fine.

17:02.777 --> 17:04.578
Can we get
some ice for that?

17:04.613 --> 17:05.779
Oh.
All right.

17:07.449 --> 17:09.016
Oh, God.

17:10.519 --> 17:12.720
Linette,
you are injured

17:12.753 --> 17:14.588
and you're not
taking care of yourself.

17:14.623 --> 17:15.955
Don't start, Lacey.

17:15.991 --> 17:17.625
No. You're gonna listen
to me.

17:17.659 --> 17:19.894
You need to take some time off,
and while you're at it,

17:19.928 --> 17:21.795
would you just
move in with Riley already?

17:21.829 --> 17:24.064
She needs your help
as much as you need hers.

17:24.098 --> 17:25.965
I don't need Riley's help.
Shut it.

17:26.001 --> 17:29.036
Just 'cause you're asking
for help does not make you weak.

17:29.070 --> 17:31.438
You raised Riley.
You pretty much raised me.

17:31.473 --> 17:33.741
You're one of
the strongest women I know.

17:33.775 --> 17:35.976
I just don't want
to be a burden.

17:36.011 --> 17:37.378
You're family.

17:37.412 --> 17:40.814
You'll always be a burden.
[ Chuckles ]

17:40.849 --> 17:43.150
But at least with family,
you'll never be alone.

17:43.184 --> 17:45.152
Okay?

17:45.186 --> 17:46.020
Ouch!

17:47.489 --> 17:48.789
I'm sorry.

17:48.823 --> 17:50.958
I'm sorry.

17:50.992 --> 17:52.927
Class!
A-ten-hut!

17:52.961 --> 17:56.263
You are alone!

17:56.298 --> 17:58.599
No one can help you!

17:58.633 --> 18:01.268
At least that's what cadets
who fail this Academy think!

18:01.303 --> 18:04.805
Every decision that you make
as a police officer

18:04.839 --> 18:07.508
affects everyone else here.

18:07.542 --> 18:11.111
We are your partners,
and we act as a team!

18:11.146 --> 18:12.913
Is that understood?
All: Sir, yes, sir!

18:12.948 --> 18:15.015
Instructor: I can't hear you!
All: Sir, yes, sir!

18:15.050 --> 18:19.086
Instructor:
Now, everyone, give me 15 laps.

18:19.120 --> 18:21.722
Move! Move!
[ Whistle blows ]

18:25.894 --> 18:27.361
Trimble: Looks like
they'll let anybody

18:27.395 --> 18:29.330
in the police academy
these days.

18:29.364 --> 18:31.031
Even a felon's brother.

18:31.066 --> 18:33.000
Still the same dick
you were in high school.

18:33.034 --> 18:34.635
When are you gonna grow up,
Trimble?

18:34.669 --> 18:36.036
What?
You gonna shiv me?

18:36.071 --> 18:37.371
Hey, hey! You punch him
and you're out.

18:37.405 --> 18:38.639
That's exactly
what Trimble wants.

18:38.673 --> 18:39.873
Don't do it.

18:39.908 --> 18:42.810
I told you maggots
to move!

18:42.844 --> 18:44.712
15 extra laps for both of you!

18:44.746 --> 18:46.480
Move!

18:46.514 --> 18:48.382
You okay?
Yeah, I'm fine.

18:48.416 --> 18:50.718
Shelby,
in case you're wondering.

18:50.752 --> 18:53.721
Evan. Thanks for
talking me down. Yes, I was.

18:53.755 --> 18:55.823
Trimble's
an entitled prick.

18:55.857 --> 18:57.291
Just beat his ass
when no one's watching.

18:57.325 --> 18:58.525
Come on, people!

18:58.560 --> 19:00.060
Want to race?

19:00.095 --> 19:03.030
I know
you're not slowing down!

19:03.064 --> 19:04.331
Move!

19:38.122 --> 19:40.323
What the hell
are you doing in here?

19:40.358 --> 19:41.925
Selena, hey,
I ran out of lavender oil,

19:41.959 --> 19:43.159
and I thought that --
Bull!

19:43.194 --> 19:44.628
You're going through
my stuff, huh?

19:44.662 --> 19:46.363
What are you
looking for?

19:46.397 --> 19:47.731
I don't know
what you're talking about.

19:47.765 --> 19:49.266
Oh, don't play
that innocent crap with me.

19:49.300 --> 19:50.934
I am on to you, girl.
What is your problem?

19:50.968 --> 19:52.302
I swear, if I catch you going
near me or my things again...

19:52.336 --> 19:53.770
You have been nothing
but nasty to me

19:53.771 --> 19:55.007
since the first day
that I got here.

19:55.032 --> 19:56.014
...I will rip your
damn head off!

19:56.015 --> 19:57.883
Hey!

19:57.917 --> 20:00.252
Good Lord, what is going on in
here? Everybody can hear y'all.

20:00.286 --> 20:01.954
Caught the bitch
breaking into my room,

20:01.988 --> 20:04.656
going through my things.
Riley, it's not what you think.

20:04.691 --> 20:06.892
Okay, look, Nikki, everyone here
deserves their privacy.

20:06.926 --> 20:08.594
Now, what were you doing
in Selena's room?

20:08.628 --> 20:10.763
Oh, I know exactly
what she's doing in here.

20:10.797 --> 20:13.398
Same reason she tried
to break into your office

20:13.433 --> 20:16.068
and jimmy open my lock.
She's a thief.

20:16.102 --> 20:17.945
[ Sighs ]
I want her gone, Riley.

20:17.946 --> 20:19.121
You don't trust me,
either?

20:19.122 --> 20:20.113
I'm gonna ask you again --

20:20.138 --> 20:21.817
what were you
doing in Selena's room?

20:21.818 --> 20:23.218
Whoa. I thought
we were a family here.

20:23.252 --> 20:24.653
Isn't that what
you're always telling us?

20:24.687 --> 20:26.955
Back home, I'd borrow things
from my sisters,

20:26.990 --> 20:28.957
but I'd always replace
whatever I took.

20:28.992 --> 20:30.659
I ain't your sister.
Riley: Hey.

20:30.693 --> 20:31.994
Back down, Selena.

20:32.028 --> 20:33.495
I thought
you were different, Riley.

20:33.529 --> 20:34.796
Look, Nikki, I --

20:34.831 --> 20:36.965
You think
that I'm a thief.

20:37.000 --> 20:38.367
[ Voice breaking ]
That's fine.

20:38.401 --> 20:39.835
You can think
whatever you want.

20:39.869 --> 20:41.069
I don't care.

20:41.104 --> 20:43.405
I quit.

20:43.439 --> 20:45.073
Wow.

20:45.108 --> 20:47.542
[ Sighs ]

20:51.312 --> 20:52.512
[ Glass clinks ]

20:52.546 --> 20:54.514
Here.
$1,000.

20:54.548 --> 20:57.951
You're one step closer
to owning the Rub.

20:57.985 --> 21:00.854
Yeah, on a day like today, I
might just get buyer's remorse.

21:00.888 --> 21:03.156
What made you hire Nikki
in the first place,

21:03.190 --> 21:04.457
apart from
that size "C" cup?

21:04.492 --> 21:05.792
I went with my gut,

21:05.826 --> 21:07.961
just like you did
when you hired me.

21:07.995 --> 21:10.363
You know,
she reminded me a lot of myself.

21:10.397 --> 21:13.299
Lost and scared and just
hoping to land on her feet.

21:13.334 --> 21:15.735
Well, a lot of people land.
Some don't.

21:15.769 --> 21:17.504
Yeah, anyway,
I need to talk to her.

21:17.538 --> 21:19.005
I've been trying
to call her.

21:19.039 --> 21:20.874
You know,
you are the boss now,

21:20.908 --> 21:23.009
and you are gonna
drive yourself crazy

21:23.043 --> 21:25.845
if you struggle over
every situation like this.

21:25.880 --> 21:28.982
Now, the girl quit.
That's on her.

21:29.016 --> 21:32.185
The best that you can do
is just let her go.

21:45.599 --> 21:48.668
Take those boxes
down the hall to the left.

21:48.702 --> 21:51.571
I mean, do people
actually enjoy baking?

21:51.605 --> 21:54.207
This is more confusing
than Travis' science projects.

21:54.241 --> 21:56.209
You really are
moving in a lot of stuff.

21:56.243 --> 21:57.844
Are you
having second thoughts?

21:57.878 --> 22:00.380
No. Not at all.
I'm glad you decided to do it.

22:00.414 --> 22:02.148
Where are
the children?

22:02.183 --> 22:04.884
I was looking forward to seeing
Katie half-covered in meringue.

22:04.919 --> 22:06.586
Yeah, well,
they're still upset

22:06.620 --> 22:08.388
about not being able
to see Kyle.

22:08.422 --> 22:11.858
I mean, he's gonna be gone
for a bit.

22:11.892 --> 22:13.860
You're not still thinking about
taking them to the jail,

22:13.894 --> 22:15.094
are you?

22:15.129 --> 22:16.663
Definitely thinking
about it.

22:16.697 --> 22:19.365
Look, mama, they miss
their daddy, you know?

22:19.400 --> 22:21.501
I just want to
do right by them.

22:21.535 --> 22:23.236
Put that down
and listen to me.

22:24.572 --> 22:27.774
Do you remember when Lacey moved
in with us when you were kids?

22:27.808 --> 22:30.243
Oh, yeah, when her daddy left
and her mama --

22:30.277 --> 22:31.511
Falling down drunk.

22:31.545 --> 22:34.147
Now, I'm gonna tell it
like it is.

22:36.317 --> 22:38.518
All those nights,
I held Lacey in my arms

22:38.552 --> 22:40.353
while she cried herself
to sleep.

22:40.387 --> 22:42.188
Yeah, I remember
her being so sad.

22:42.223 --> 22:43.723
She could never
see the good in her mom.

22:43.757 --> 22:45.291
All she could see
was the trouble her mom was in.

22:45.326 --> 22:47.227
Now, don't do that
to Katie and Travis.

22:47.261 --> 22:48.962
Don't take them
down to that jail.

22:48.996 --> 22:51.764
Let them keep their --
their good memories of Kyle.

23:01.342 --> 23:02.976
Hey, Nikki.
Still trying to reach you.

23:03.010 --> 23:04.444
Will you
call me back?

23:04.478 --> 23:06.045
You have no idea
how persistent I am. Call me.

23:06.080 --> 23:07.614
Nikki still hasn't
called you back?

23:07.648 --> 23:09.449
No. I think
we might have misjudged her.

23:09.483 --> 23:11.884
I never thought I'd say these
words, but you might be right.

23:11.919 --> 23:14.821
She sent me these.
Hello, it's after 3:45.

23:14.855 --> 23:16.756
I had a 3:30 with Derek.
Check this out.

23:16.790 --> 23:18.324
"Sorry for
going into your room.

23:18.359 --> 23:20.393
I'd never steal from you.
Take care. Nikki."

23:20.427 --> 23:21.628
He's running
20 minutes late?

23:21.662 --> 23:23.396
I'm not waiting for this
any longer.

23:23.430 --> 23:25.331
Ma'am, if you just give it
a sec, I can talk to my boss.

23:25.366 --> 23:26.666
Hey.
What was that?

23:26.700 --> 23:28.668
Derek --
he took on a new client, Lisa,

23:28.702 --> 23:30.970
and this is the second time
he's gone overtime

23:31.005 --> 23:32.405
with her this week.

23:32.439 --> 23:34.140
I'm guessing that's Lisa.
The one and only.

23:34.174 --> 23:35.508
[ Scoffs ]

23:35.542 --> 23:37.944
Well, doesn't Lisa
look extra relaxed?

23:37.978 --> 23:40.780
I think our cowboy's
running a little side business.

23:40.814 --> 23:43.716
Hey, Derek, can I talk to you
in my office for a sec?

23:46.720 --> 23:48.588
[ Laughs ] He's in trouble.
Mm-hmm.

23:48.622 --> 23:50.189
What made you think
that you could run

23:50.224 --> 23:52.258
your own happy-endings
side business under my roof

23:52.293 --> 23:53.493
without me
finding out?

23:53.527 --> 23:55.128
I don't know
what you're talking about.

23:55.162 --> 23:56.729
Don't play games with me.

24:02.036 --> 24:04.370
I was just as surprised
as anyone

24:04.405 --> 24:07.040
when Lisa asked me
for a happy ending.

24:07.074 --> 24:10.510
And at first I thought
it was just a one-time thing,

24:10.544 --> 24:13.046
but then
she kept asking for it.

24:13.080 --> 24:14.314
[ Sighs ]

24:14.348 --> 24:15.782
I thought
I wasn't hurting anyone,

24:15.816 --> 24:17.817
and you're always telling us
to make people happy.

24:17.851 --> 24:20.953
And you didn't think
I'd have any concerns?

24:20.988 --> 24:24.023
I just
plain didn't think.

24:24.058 --> 24:26.526
I'll pack up my stuff,
and I'll get out of here.

24:26.560 --> 24:28.661
Please just don't
call the cops, okay?

24:28.696 --> 24:30.630
Oh, Lord.
I'm not calling the cops.

24:30.664 --> 24:32.198
Thank you.
I knew you'd understand.

24:32.232 --> 24:34.200
I mean,
if I got propositioned,

24:34.234 --> 24:37.070
hell, I'm sure you guys
get hit up all the time.

24:37.104 --> 24:38.705
Oh, yeah, we do.

24:38.739 --> 24:40.807
So,
how do you handle it?

24:40.841 --> 24:45.411
By following
a very specific set of rules.

24:45.446 --> 24:46.913
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Wait a minute.

24:46.947 --> 24:48.881
Does that mean that you --
Listen and learn.

24:48.916 --> 24:50.483
You're serious.

24:50.517 --> 24:51.784
Deadly serious.

24:53.554 --> 24:55.555
First rule is, if you're
gonna service your clients,

24:55.589 --> 24:57.390
you don't talk about
servicing your clients.

24:57.424 --> 24:59.726
Second rule is, you go back
and you recheck rule number one.

24:59.760 --> 25:01.594
Am I
making myself clear?

25:01.628 --> 25:03.096
Crystal.
Okay.

25:03.130 --> 25:04.731
I'm gonna talk to Lisa
and your other clients

25:04.765 --> 25:06.432
and make sure they know
which rules they're following.

25:06.467 --> 25:08.668
That's not a problem.
Then I'm gonna raise your room rent.

25:08.702 --> 25:10.169
Anything you make on tips,
you can keep.

25:10.204 --> 25:11.704
Did you want to say anything?
Any questions?

25:11.739 --> 25:13.005
[ Laughs ]

25:13.040 --> 25:15.041
Just that I landed
the best job ever.

25:15.075 --> 25:16.542
[ Laughs ]

25:16.577 --> 25:20.847
Yeah, don't ever hide anything
from me again.

25:23.917 --> 25:27.086
Wow. I am so glad I don't have
to keep this a secret anymore.

25:27.121 --> 25:28.855
Only one who knew
was Nikki.

25:28.889 --> 25:30.223
Yeah, well,
she never said anything.

25:30.257 --> 25:31.557
I know.
That's why I trusted her.

25:31.592 --> 25:34.026
Have you seen her
since she quit?

25:34.061 --> 25:35.828
Actually,
well, yeah.

25:35.863 --> 25:37.787
I'm gonna see her tonight.

25:37.788 --> 25:39.118
She called this morning
and asked me to come by

25:39.143 --> 25:40.967
after work to help her move.

25:40.968 --> 25:42.335
She's getting evicted.

25:42.369 --> 25:44.704
I'm coming with you.

25:45.973 --> 25:48.107
Now get out.

25:58.118 --> 25:59.852
This is her place.

25:59.887 --> 26:01.721
Said she'd be home
from work by 7:00.

26:01.755 --> 26:03.556
Wait a minute.
She's got another job already?

26:03.590 --> 26:05.525
Well, sort of. She's back
working at the club

26:05.559 --> 26:07.693
where she used to dance
before she came to the Rub.

26:07.728 --> 26:09.562
Stuck her on the day shift,
and she's not making crap.

26:09.596 --> 26:10.830
[ Tires screech ]

26:13.400 --> 26:14.734
Carlyle:
Listen to me.

26:14.768 --> 26:16.102
Just listen to me
when I talk to you!

26:16.136 --> 26:17.904
Get back in this car!
Nikki, don't!

26:17.938 --> 26:19.472
Nikki,
get back here!

26:19.506 --> 26:21.974
Nikki, get back here! I'm serious!
Give it up!

26:22.009 --> 26:23.242
Carlyle: Nikki,
get back here!

26:23.277 --> 26:24.777
Oh, my God.
Get back here!

26:24.812 --> 26:26.546
Don't walk away from me!
I'm serious!

26:26.580 --> 26:28.114
Let me go!
Look at me!

26:28.148 --> 26:30.616
Look at me!
[ Horn blares ]

26:32.786 --> 26:35.822
Riley, wait, wait!
Hang on!

26:35.856 --> 26:37.290
Riley!

26:37.324 --> 26:38.558
Hey!

26:39.542 --> 26:41.015
Riley: Hey!
Are you kidding me?

26:41.115 --> 26:43.250
Nikki: Leave me alone!
Riley: Hey!

26:43.935 --> 26:45.336
No!
I'm not done with you!

26:45.370 --> 26:46.670
Stop!
Nikki, no.

26:46.705 --> 26:48.138
You're gonna push around
a girl, scumbag?

26:48.173 --> 26:49.494
Take me out!
Get back in your car!

26:49.507 --> 26:50.741
You have no idea.
Now, get out of here!

26:50.775 --> 26:52.343
[ Tires squeal ]
Are you okay?

26:52.377 --> 26:54.211
I'm fine!
What are you doing here?

26:54.245 --> 26:55.779
I trusted you, Derek!

26:55.814 --> 26:56.847
Well, I'm sorry, but when
you didn't call me back,

26:56.881 --> 26:58.315
I got a little worried.

26:58.350 --> 26:59.831
Who is that guy, huh?
Your boyfriend?

26:59.856 --> 27:00.551
No.

27:00.552 --> 27:01.919
Well, whoever he is,
we should call the police

27:01.953 --> 27:03.153
'cause we
just saw him hit you.

27:03.188 --> 27:04.688
No, you can't the cops.
Please!

27:04.723 --> 27:06.323
Listen to me.
I've got two kids at home,

27:06.358 --> 27:08.025
and I'm putting myself in danger
by being out here.

27:08.059 --> 27:09.660
Now,
you better talk to me.

27:09.694 --> 27:13.597
You know how I used to strip
before I was working for you?

27:13.631 --> 27:15.299
Well,
I swore I'd never go back,

27:15.333 --> 27:18.268
but when I quit, I needed a job
fast, so I called my old boss.

27:18.303 --> 27:19.703
The guy
who just roughed you up?

27:19.738 --> 27:21.105
His name is Greg Carlyle.

27:21.139 --> 27:23.707
He owns Wild Nights
off of highway 59.

27:23.742 --> 27:25.976
Are you kidding me?
You're working at Wild Nights?

27:26.011 --> 27:27.211
That place
is very dangerous.

27:27.245 --> 27:28.679
I had
nowhere else to go.

27:28.713 --> 27:30.948
I was almost two months behind
on my rent.

27:30.982 --> 27:32.316
I was about to be evicted.

27:32.350 --> 27:34.385
I don't have $1,500.

27:34.419 --> 27:37.454
So, I called Carlyle, and
I begged him for my job back.

27:37.489 --> 27:39.289
So now
you don't have to move?

27:39.324 --> 27:41.658
[ Sighs ]
I worked it out.

27:41.693 --> 27:43.961
God, I had no idea
you were this behind.

27:43.995 --> 27:45.963
When I started working
at the Rub,

27:45.997 --> 27:49.666
I saw a future for myself
for the first time in my life.

27:49.701 --> 27:51.668
And when Carlyle paid my rent,

27:51.703 --> 27:54.238
he made me
drop out of school again.

27:54.272 --> 27:57.474
Treats me like he owns me.

27:57.509 --> 28:00.344
Hey. We're gonna figure
this out, okay?

28:00.378 --> 28:02.579
No!
[ Sniffles ]

28:02.614 --> 28:04.848
He is never
gonna let me go --

28:04.883 --> 28:06.150
not again.

28:06.184 --> 28:08.719
You have no idea
what he is capable of.

28:08.753 --> 28:10.554
Nikki, Nikki,
I can protect you.

28:10.588 --> 28:14.091
You've already
done enough harm.

28:14.125 --> 28:15.592
Just leave me alone.

28:23.768 --> 28:26.403
[ Dog barks,
Travis and Katie shouting ]

28:26.438 --> 28:28.105
Linette: Just a smooch more
to the left.

28:28.139 --> 28:29.873
I'm pretty sure
when Riley asked you to move in,

28:29.908 --> 28:32.176
that didn't include
rearranging the family photos.

28:32.210 --> 28:33.911
Less discussing
and more rearranging.

28:33.945 --> 28:35.312
Just a tap more
to the left.

28:37.148 --> 28:38.849
There.
That's perfect.

28:38.883 --> 28:40.350
Hey, have you guys
seen the takeout menus?

28:40.385 --> 28:41.785
They were right here
in this drawer.

28:41.786 --> 28:43.353
Well, now they're by the phone
in a binder,

28:43.388 --> 28:45.522
which is where they should have
been in the first place.

28:45.557 --> 28:47.558
The kitchen, too?
I have a lot of free time.

28:47.592 --> 28:49.259
You know what, mama? I've got
way too much on my plate

28:49.294 --> 28:51.395
to not be able to find
the pie palace menu.

28:51.429 --> 28:53.864
I thought you were baking the pie.
Never gonna happen.

28:53.898 --> 28:55.399
What is this obsession
with pies these days?

28:55.433 --> 28:57.601
Is there something
you're not telling me?

28:57.635 --> 28:59.405
You know what? You can
rearrange my whole house

28:59.430 --> 29:00.270
but not my whole life.

29:00.271 --> 29:01.772
Travis: I want to
read this one!

29:01.806 --> 29:03.040
Kids!
Mama!

29:03.074 --> 29:05.409
Read it!
Kids!

29:07.879 --> 29:09.346
[ Sighs ]

29:09.380 --> 29:10.781
Riley.

29:13.551 --> 29:14.952
[ Clears throat ]

29:14.986 --> 29:18.122
You guys
doing okay in there?

29:18.156 --> 29:20.095
Yes, ma'am. We're trying
to read dad's letters,

29:20.120 --> 29:21.058
if you don't mind.

29:21.059 --> 29:23.193
Okay, so, is this one of those
moments where you need mama,

29:23.228 --> 29:24.461
or do you want to be alone?

29:25.130 --> 29:27.131
Alone, please.

29:27.165 --> 29:29.433
Fair enough.

29:31.836 --> 29:34.671
Where is the phone?

29:40.278 --> 29:41.945
Just keep breathing.

29:41.980 --> 29:44.414
You're doing great.

29:44.449 --> 29:48.318
[ Sighs ]

29:48.353 --> 29:51.989
Okay.
What's going on?

29:52.023 --> 29:55.159
I don't know.
Nothing.

29:55.193 --> 29:57.561
[ Scoffs ]
Don't "nothing" me.

29:57.595 --> 29:59.563
You got a world of hurt
on your shoulders.

29:59.597 --> 30:02.766
It's just
with Kyle back...

30:02.800 --> 30:06.837
I don't know why,
but it just feels...strange.

30:06.871 --> 30:08.472
Of course
it feels strange.

30:08.506 --> 30:12.442
You and Evan?
It's complicated.

30:12.477 --> 30:14.811
Well, that is
putting it mildly.

30:14.846 --> 30:18.315
It's completely natural
to feel conflicted.

30:18.349 --> 30:19.816
But Evan loves you,

30:19.851 --> 30:21.985
and the best thing you can do
is be honest with him,

30:22.020 --> 30:23.587
how you feel.

30:23.621 --> 30:28.525
That's the hard part --
figuring out how I feel.

30:28.560 --> 30:30.294
[ Chuckles softly ]

30:30.328 --> 30:33.964
Anyway, I'm just --
I'm -- I'm, you know,

30:33.998 --> 30:39.036
worried about the kids 'cause
they miss their daddy so much,

30:39.070 --> 30:42.506
and he's gonna be
in jail for so long.

30:42.540 --> 30:45.809
And [sighs] I don't know
what to do.

30:45.843 --> 30:48.946
You are
an incredible mother...

30:48.980 --> 30:51.982
And you'll figure it out.

30:52.016 --> 30:56.053
You know, mama told me
how hard it was for you

30:56.087 --> 31:00.490
to watch your mama
go through all of her troubles,

31:00.525 --> 31:02.125
all the crying,
and...

31:02.160 --> 31:05.295
I just want to protect
Katie and Travis from that.

31:05.330 --> 31:08.732
Well, Linette means well,
but she shouldn't speak for me.

31:08.766 --> 31:10.200
Those are my memories.

31:10.235 --> 31:14.004
Sure, it was hard watching
my mama go through hell,

31:14.038 --> 31:17.207
but it was better
than not seeing her at all.

31:24.682 --> 31:25.949
Whoa!
[ Laughs ]

31:25.984 --> 31:27.884
Where'd you learn
how to kick like that?

31:27.919 --> 31:29.519
My Uncle taught me.

31:29.554 --> 31:31.355
We used to go one-on-one
all the time

31:31.389 --> 31:33.323
back home in Louisiana
when I was a kid.

31:33.358 --> 31:34.558
You guys
still close?

31:34.592 --> 31:36.960
He died
when I was 16.

31:36.995 --> 31:39.529
Great guy.
Even better left winger.

31:39.564 --> 31:41.698
Mind if I ask
how he passed?

31:41.733 --> 31:45.202
Yeah, I do.

31:45.236 --> 31:47.004
Sorry.
Didn't mean to pry.

31:47.038 --> 31:50.641
No, there's just some things
I want to keep private.

31:50.675 --> 31:53.543
[ Sighs ]

31:53.578 --> 31:55.618
I know a lot of people
don't want you in the academy

31:55.647 --> 31:56.847
because of your brother.

31:56.881 --> 31:59.449
The way I see it...

31:59.484 --> 32:01.018
[ Sniffs ]

32:01.052 --> 32:02.886
...everyone
deserves a chance.

32:02.920 --> 32:07.024
Can't hold anyone's family
against them.

32:08.826 --> 32:11.128
Come on.
What are you waiting for?

32:13.498 --> 32:14.998
[ Chuckles ]

32:15.033 --> 32:16.733
All right.

32:21.472 --> 32:23.707
I really want to give you
a second chance, Kyle,

32:23.741 --> 32:26.009
but I have got to know
what happened in Mexico.

32:26.044 --> 32:27.477
Nothing.
Nothing happened.

32:27.512 --> 32:29.346
Then why would they revoke
your bail?

32:29.380 --> 32:31.682
When I was down there,
I bought pills. All right?

32:31.716 --> 32:33.216
I didn't sell them.
[ Sighs ]

32:33.251 --> 32:35.218
I really
want to believe you.

32:35.253 --> 32:36.787
Riley,
I slipped up.

32:36.821 --> 32:38.822
All right?
But I am clean now.

32:38.856 --> 32:41.124
And I am never
going back to that.

32:41.159 --> 32:42.392
All right?
I promise.

32:42.427 --> 32:43.760
[ Door buzzes ]

32:45.863 --> 32:47.931
How are Travis and Katie doing
with all this?

32:49.901 --> 32:51.835
How are Travis
and Katie?

32:51.869 --> 32:54.504
They're awful.
They miss their daddy.

32:54.539 --> 32:56.673
I would never
hurt them.

32:56.708 --> 32:58.575
You did
when you left.

33:01.579 --> 33:04.681
Look, all I can do
is say that I'm sorry.

33:04.716 --> 33:06.216
All right?

33:06.250 --> 33:11.188
And then prove myself to you
and them every single day.

33:13.424 --> 33:18.595
But in order to do that,
I need my family with me.

33:21.199 --> 33:24.901
You got to let me
see our kids.

33:34.112 --> 33:36.413
Hi.
Hey.

33:36.447 --> 33:38.448
[ Scoffs ]

33:38.483 --> 33:40.117
You at least
try to bake them?

33:40.151 --> 33:41.618
Yes,
actually, I did.

33:41.652 --> 33:43.754
And I appreciate the recipes,
but let's be honest --

33:43.788 --> 33:45.389
these sploshing pies
are the last thing

33:45.423 --> 33:46.690
I need to be worried
about.

33:46.724 --> 33:48.625
Yeah, I hear you.
What'd you buy?

33:48.659 --> 33:50.527
Ooh,
I went with creamy.

33:50.561 --> 33:53.964
Lemon meringue and Boston cream
so he has a choice.

33:53.998 --> 33:56.466
Nice. Nice. See,
I draw the line at rice pudding.

33:56.501 --> 33:58.535
Those damn kernels
get stuck in places

33:58.569 --> 33:59.890
you don't even
want to know about.

33:59.904 --> 34:01.104
Uh, yeah.

34:01.139 --> 34:03.407
Look, we need
to discuss Nikki.

34:03.441 --> 34:04.708
She's in trouble.

34:04.742 --> 34:06.543
Punky Brewster
get knocked up?

34:06.577 --> 34:07.844
Derek and I
went to see her,

34:07.879 --> 34:09.379
and she's working
over at Wild Nights.

34:09.414 --> 34:11.882
She crazy?
That guy's so messed up.

34:11.916 --> 34:13.784
Well, she said she didn't have
anywhere else to go,

34:13.818 --> 34:15.284
and now she's in debt
to him.

34:15.319 --> 34:17.420
I may not have wanted
that girl around here,

34:17.455 --> 34:19.089
but nobody
deserves Carlyle.

34:19.123 --> 34:21.358
Look, I know that you hate to
admit it, but we are a family.

34:21.391 --> 34:22.826
She needs our help.

34:22.860 --> 34:25.896
What do you want to do?

34:25.929 --> 34:27.898
[ Sighs ]

34:27.931 --> 34:31.701
[ Dance music plays ]

34:38.141 --> 34:40.141
What makes you think
Carlyle's gonna listen to you?

34:40.143 --> 34:42.879
Because he's just like everybody
else -- driven by money.

34:42.914 --> 34:45.181
Maybe he's gonna take your money
and screw us.

34:45.216 --> 34:46.616
Not this time.

34:46.650 --> 34:48.717
[ Vehicle approaches ]

34:59.997 --> 35:02.766
There he is.

35:04.569 --> 35:08.071
[ Sighs ]

35:11.309 --> 35:13.910
Hey!

35:13.945 --> 35:16.079
Hey, dollface.

35:16.113 --> 35:17.447
We want to see Nikki.

35:17.482 --> 35:19.883
I want to see the money.
Nikki first.

35:19.917 --> 35:21.151
[ Sighs ]

35:34.131 --> 35:35.732
I'm so sorry,
Riley.

35:35.766 --> 35:38.702
I didn't mean
to drag you into this.

35:38.736 --> 35:42.639
Where's the money?
$1,500.

35:42.673 --> 35:44.474
Right here
and Nikki comes with me.

35:44.509 --> 35:45.742
Nice.

35:45.776 --> 35:47.677
Deal's changed.

35:48.980 --> 35:50.447
I forgot the interest.

35:50.481 --> 35:52.549
It's gonna be
another $2,000.

35:52.583 --> 35:54.317
Yeah,
that's not gonna happen.

35:56.687 --> 35:59.489
[ Tires screech ]

36:03.427 --> 36:05.362
Ladies.

36:06.764 --> 36:07.964
Is there
a problem here?

36:07.999 --> 36:09.499
No,
everything's great.

36:09.534 --> 36:12.235
Mr. Carlyle, have you met
my friend, Detective Monroe?

36:12.270 --> 36:13.970
I'm afraid
I haven't had the pleasure,

36:14.005 --> 36:15.939
but I do have a lot of friends
on the force.

36:15.973 --> 36:17.440
Really?
I'd love to meet them.

36:17.475 --> 36:18.755
Why don't you
give me their names

36:18.776 --> 36:20.176
and we'll all
get to know each other.

36:20.211 --> 36:21.745
Maybe set up
a bowling league.

36:21.779 --> 36:23.613
[ Scoffs ]
Everything all right, ma'am?

36:23.648 --> 36:24.848
Oh, she's fine.

36:24.882 --> 36:26.683
I was asking
the lady.

36:26.717 --> 36:28.952
She was just
coming with me.

36:32.723 --> 36:34.991
Come on, Nikki.

36:35.026 --> 36:36.493
Let's go.

36:42.800 --> 36:45.702
[ Sighs ]

36:45.736 --> 36:48.171
I'm so bummed,
but I have to go.

36:48.205 --> 36:49.506
Take care, Riley.

36:49.540 --> 36:50.974
I'm just gonna hang back

36:51.008 --> 36:52.776
and get to know my friends
a little better.

36:52.810 --> 36:54.277
It's always a pleasure,
Mrs. Parks.

36:54.312 --> 36:57.847
I'm sure I'll be seeing you
real soon.

36:57.882 --> 37:00.283
Night, y'all.

37:13.770 --> 37:16.140
Thank God your detective friend
showed up when he did.

37:16.240 --> 37:18.140
Did you think I would have gone
in there without a backup plan?

37:18.175 --> 37:19.775
Do I look
completely insane?

37:19.810 --> 37:21.171
Nobody's ever
cared about me enough

37:21.178 --> 37:23.145
to do
something like that.

37:23.180 --> 37:25.081
I don't know
how to thank you.

37:25.115 --> 37:27.650
Well, you could come back
and work for me.

37:27.684 --> 37:30.219
We need you at the Rub.
Don't we, Selena?

37:31.688 --> 37:34.190
What she said, yeah.

37:34.224 --> 37:36.092
[ Laughter ]

37:36.126 --> 37:37.460
Okay, starting tonight,
we all make a pact

37:37.494 --> 37:39.428
that we trust each other,
yes?

37:39.463 --> 37:41.597
Okay, let's break this up
before we all start crying

37:41.632 --> 37:43.466
and want to braid
each other's hair.

37:43.500 --> 37:45.268
Hey.
Watch it, new guy.

37:45.302 --> 37:46.669
Come on, I'll give you guys
a ride home.

37:46.703 --> 37:47.937
All right.
Good night.

37:47.971 --> 37:49.205
Night.

37:50.807 --> 37:52.475
Thank you.

37:52.509 --> 37:55.011
Welcome.

37:56.346 --> 37:59.181
I'm just glad
you're all right.

37:59.216 --> 38:01.484
But if you think this is over,
you're fooling yourself.

38:01.518 --> 38:03.419
Guys like Carlyle --
they don't give up easy.

38:03.453 --> 38:04.654
I know that.

38:04.688 --> 38:06.355
But you know what?

38:06.390 --> 38:09.525
If I had to do it again, I would
help Nikki in a heartbeat.

38:09.559 --> 38:12.895
You just
watch your back.

38:19.703 --> 38:22.305
[ Travis and Katie
shouting indistinctly ]

38:24.708 --> 38:26.642
I'm telling mom!

38:26.677 --> 38:28.010
Can we have
some lemon meringue?

38:28.045 --> 38:29.679
Not now, baby.

38:29.713 --> 38:31.947
Those are for your mom.
Both: Hi, Mom!

38:31.982 --> 38:33.549
Oh!

38:33.583 --> 38:35.351
Hey!

38:35.385 --> 38:37.887
Mama,
what are they still doing up?

38:37.921 --> 38:40.790
I couldn't get them
out of that damn fort.

38:40.824 --> 38:42.992
Mama,
these pies look amazing.

38:43.026 --> 38:45.127
I baked them today
with my one good arm.

38:45.162 --> 38:47.129
What is all this about?

38:47.164 --> 38:48.531
It's about you.

38:48.565 --> 38:50.066
You're so sweet
to let me move in.

38:50.100 --> 38:51.634
I want you to know
I can help out.

38:51.668 --> 38:53.336
Thank you.

38:55.772 --> 38:57.707
Hey, mama,
I'm gonna --

38:57.741 --> 39:00.643
I'm gonna let the kids
go and see Kyle in jail.

39:00.677 --> 39:05.314
You know, I -- I really
appreciate your advice,

39:05.349 --> 39:07.583
but they just...

39:07.617 --> 39:10.519
They miss their daddy.

39:10.554 --> 39:12.221
You're right.

39:13.557 --> 39:15.591
You know what's best
for your kids.

39:15.625 --> 39:18.160
I managed to nurse Lacey
through her nightmares,

39:18.195 --> 39:21.430
and if Travis and Katie get
scared, I'll be there for them.

39:23.233 --> 39:25.334
And I'm here for you.

39:25.369 --> 39:28.437
That's what we do.
We're family.

39:28.472 --> 39:32.007
[ Beth Thornley's
"Everyone Falls" plays ]

39:32.042 --> 39:35.578
Now...which one of these
am I gonna try?

39:35.612 --> 39:38.347
Whichever one you want.
I won't tell.

39:38.382 --> 39:40.583
Go ahead.

39:40.617 --> 39:42.118
Ah!

39:42.152 --> 39:44.420
That's good.

39:44.454 --> 39:48.190
[ Both laugh ]
Shh!

39:48.225 --> 39:54.997
♪ Some that don't fade

39:56.600 --> 40:02.972
♪ and they read
just like a road map ♪

40:03.006 --> 40:07.209
♪ time cuts a deep track

40:07.244 --> 40:12.581
♪ through skin and vein

40:12.616 --> 40:18.988
♪ but you know
everyone falls sometimes ♪

